.TH ADM 1 "March 2026" "adm" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
adm \- display manager for TTY with Bubble Tea interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B adm
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version ]
.RB [ \-d | \-\-daemon ]
.RB [ \-c
.IR PATH | \-\-config
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-C | \-\-print-config ]
.RB [ \-i | \-\-ignore-config ]
.RB [ \-t
.IR TTY | \-\-tty
.IR TTY ]
.RB [ \-u | \-\-default-user
.IR USER ]
.RB [ \-a | \-\-autologin
.RI [ SESSION ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B adm
is a display manager inspired by
.BR emptty (1).
It presents login and session selection using a terminal UI built with
.BR bubbletea (charm.sh).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/adm/conf
System configuration.
.TP
.I ~/.config/adm
.TP
.I ~/.adm
Per-user session script or configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/pam.d/adm
PAM stack (service name
.BR adm ).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR emptty (1),
.BR agetty (8)
